			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com">Holistic Health Women&#039;s Podcasts and Radio</a></p><p style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 15px; width:240px;">
		<img src="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/SUSAN-4.jpg" width="240" />
		</p><p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: medium;">Author Susan Schenck joins holistic health talk for women radio host Irina Wardas on Wednesday, January 11th at 9:30 am PT / 12:30 pm <strong></strong>ET LIVE</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong><a href="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com/wp-content/MP3/BR25.mp3" rel="nofollow">Listen:</a> Holistic Health Talk for Women Radio Show Topic</strong>: A New Year Resolution <!-- google_ad_section_start -->Weight Loss Raw Food Diet for Healthier You</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Free Gift</strong>:</span> <span style="font-size: medium;">click to sign up for a Newsletter and get your free chapter</span> 10 Reasons to Go Raw</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong><strong><em><span style="color: #ff9900;">Live, holistic health talk for women radio and podcast streams from</span> <a href="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/NaturalCounselor" rel="nofollow">the host page</a></em></strong></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Susan Schenck is a licensed acupuncturist and has been studying nutrition for decades, since she had an eating disorder in high school. She tried dozens of diets, but when she discovered the raw food diet, she was so impressed that she had to write a book about it, a comprehensive guide, which took six years to write.<img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-1844" title="Author Susan Schenck" src="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/SUSAN-4-111x150.jpg" alt="Raw Diet" width="111" height="150" /></span><!-- google_ad_section_end --></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Susan Schenck, LAc, is a raw food coach, lecturer, and author of the 2-time award winning book, <em>The Live Food Factor,<strong> </strong>The</em> <em>Comprehensive Guide to the Ultimate Diet for Body, Mind, Spirit &amp; Planet</em>, which has gained a reputation as the encyclopedia of the raw food diet—as well as </span><em><span style="font-size: medium;">Beyond Broccoli, Creating a Biologically Balanced Diet When a Vegetarian Diet Doesn’t Work.</span><strong> </strong></em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff9900;"><strong>Callers are welcome to join the conversation: <em> (347)-857-4862</em></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Suggested Women Radio and Podcast Interview Questions</strong>:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">What are 10 reasons to stop cooking, or at least eat 80% raw?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Could you tell us some of the studies which prove that cooked food is toxic? I understand you summarize 66 studies in The Live Food Factor.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Why don&#8217;t vegan or  vegetarian diets work for everyone?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">What are 5 foods to avoid at all costs?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;"> How does eating a healthy diet make you look younger and more beautiful?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">What are some stories you have of people who “miraculously” healed from “incurable” diseases by eating a raw diet?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">What are some superfoods that should be staples in one’s diet?</span></p>
