		<description><![CDATA[<p><p><a href="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com">Holistic Health Women&#039;s Podcasts and Radio</a></p><p>Brenda Jones, the Founder of Hug Wraps and Breast Cancer Survivor joins holistic health talk for women radio host Irina Wardas on Wednesday, October 5th at 9:30 am PT / 12:30 pm ET LIVE Listen: Women’s Podcast and Health Talk Radio Show Topic: Breast Cancer Surviving; Hug Wraps for Breast Cancer Patients to Feel Warm [...]</p></p><p><a href="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com/06/breast-cancer-survivor-founder-of-hug-wraps-brenda-jones/">Breast Cancer Survivor: Founder of Hug Wraps Brenda Jones</a></p>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com">Holistic Health Women&#039;s Podcasts and Radio</a></p><p style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 15px; width:240px;">
		<img src="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/DSC0535-e1317523471533.jpg" width="240" />
		</p><p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: medium;">Brenda Jones, the Founder of Hug Wraps and Breast Cancer Survivor joins holistic health talk for women radio host Irina Wardas on Wednesday, October 5th at 9:30 am PT / 12:30 pm ET LIVE</span></p>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: medium; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong><!-- google_ad_section_start --><a href="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com/wp-content/MP3/BR9.mp3" rel="nofollow">Listen</a>: Women’s Podcast and Health Talk Radio Show Topic</strong>: </span><span style="font-size: medium;">Breast Cancer Surviving; Hug Wraps for Breast Cancer Patients to Feel Warm<span id="more-1247"></span><!-- google_ad_section_end --></span></h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong><strong><em><span style="color: #ff9900;">Live,  health talk for women radio and  podcast streams from</span> <a href="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/NaturalCounselor" rel="nofollow">the host page</a></em></strong></strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: medium;">At the age of 50, Brenda Jones was diagnosed with breast cancer.  Her world fell apart.  She went from one Dr appointment to the next, endure a multitude of tests, scans and biopsy.  Next came the surgeries then painful physical therapy.  By the time she reached radiation treatments in 1/09, she admits to being a VERY angry cancer patient.  The last straw came on the first day of radiation treatments.  Brenda despised having to put on those hideous hospital gowns for daily treatments.  The solution?  Brenda designed and created a hospital gown alternative to wear instead!  No longer would she be cold, uncomfortable and humiliated.<img class="size-full wp-image-1248 alignright" title="Hug Wraps for Breast Cancer Patients" src="http://www.holistichealthtalkradioforwomen.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/DSC0535.jpg" alt="Breast Cancer Survivor: Founder of Hug Wraps Brenda Jones" width="300" height="201" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">With the help of a friend who taught her how to sew, Brenda made a kimono style wrap and picked out a cheerful and fun pattern and used flannel material so it would keep her warm in the often cold hospital treatment areas. She called this her <a href="http://www.hugwraps.org" rel="nofollow">Hug Wrap</a>.  When she wore it for the first time to treatment, the other patients started noticing and commenting on her design.  She soon began making them for the other patients…and has not stopped.  To date she has made close to 500 and Hug Wraps is now a 501c(3) Non-Profit Corporation.  Her ultimate goal is to reach out to other cancer patients everywhere and give them back their dignity while wrapping them in a nice warm HUG.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff9900;"><strong>Callers are welcome to join the conversation:  <em> (347)-857-4862</em></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Suggested</strong><strong> Women Radio and Podcast Interview Questions</strong>:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">The story / journey as a breast cancer survivor</span>&#8230;</p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">What are Hug Wraps?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Who are the recipients of Hug Wraps? </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Who produces the Hug Wraps and where are they distributed?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">How can someone order a Hug Wrap for themselves, a friend or loved one?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">I understand that you are the founder.  Please tell us how you came to start this charity/</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">If someone wants more information on Hug Wraps, how would they go about contacting you?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: medium;">What other non-profit organizations have you supported so far?</span></p>
